00:04:41.980 --> 00:04:48.380
a control. We did see that we were able to, as expected, deplete the TRBC1 positive T cells,

00:04:48.500 --> 00:04:52.680
both the malignant and the healthy cells. And you can see in the very bottom right there that

00:04:52.680 --> 00:05:01.360
the TRBC2 positive T cells were actually maintained. In mouse studies, we used this

00:05:01.360 --> 00:05:06.040
approach. There were a few different cell lines, but using GRCAT cell lines, H9 cell lines,

00:05:06.180 --> 00:05:14.680
and evaluated this by looking at those two different ADCs in addition to a control ADC.

00:05:15.160 --> 00:05:21.780
These were nude mice that were injected with TRBC1 positive cell lines that also expressed

00:05:21.780 --> 00:05:26.840
GFP and luciferase to allow for bioluminescence evaluation. And you can see in the first lane,

00:05:27.020 --> 00:05:31.940
this would include those with the control. The second lane, those who had the MMAE payload,

00:05:32.100 --> 00:05:36.160
and the third, the PBD payload, and a total of two treatments.

00:05:36.180 --> 00:05:41.980
For these mice. And at the end, these mice were alive, particularly in the third population,

00:05:42.520 --> 00:05:49.560
and without evidence of recurrence. We then evaluated a TRBC2 positive

00:05:49.560 --> 00:05:58.940
directed ADC using a similar approach. And again, in vitro work, looking at the same cell lines

00:05:58.940 --> 00:06:04.500
with a similar outcome, except this time depleting the TRBC2 positive cells and allowing for

00:06:04.500 --> 00:06:06.160
persistence of the TRBC1 positive cells. And again, in vitro work, looking at the same cell lines

00:06:06.160 --> 00:06:13.620
We used patient samples as well that were collected for those with circulating disease

00:06:13.620 --> 00:06:22.420
that had TRBC2 positive T cell lymphomas. And again, the same approach using the mice

00:06:22.420 --> 00:06:29.100
and evaluating this with the pyrolabinzidazepine payload, which looked to be the most potent in

00:06:29.100 --> 00:06:34.980
this particular study for our preclinical evaluation. These are two different cell lines

00:06:34.980 --> 00:06:36.140
that were evaluated. And again, in vitro work, looking at the same cell lines with a similar outcome,

00:06:36.160 --> 00:06:37.860
with similar responses.

00:06:40.040 --> 00:06:46.580
So in summary, TRBC1 and TRBC2 are potential targets that we believe are worth pursuing

00:06:46.580 --> 00:06:51.660
for antibody-based therapies in T cell lymphomas. There are some unique challenges with CAR-T cell

00:06:51.660 --> 00:06:54.860
therapy. I think there are some very creative ways to get around these, which we're going to

00:06:54.860 --> 00:06:59.780
hear about later, which are very exciting. But ADCs, we believe, also has a role in this situation

00:06:59.780 --> 00:07:06.140
and might allow us to not have the problems of fratricide and the killing of T cell lymphomas.

00:07:06.140 --> 00:07:08.240
So we're going to have to see if we can do something bidirectionally that we sometimes see with these

00:07:08.240 --> 00:07:10.660
CAR-T products. Thank you.
